Constructor: used to initialize an object with required values

Rules:
1. Constuctor name must be same as class name
2. No return type
3. Execute Automatically
4. Used once per object creation

Constructor Types:
1. Default Constructor: No constructor is written, Java automatically creates one.
2. No-Args Constructor: Developer writes a Constructor with zero parameters.
3. Parameterized Constructor: Developer writes a constructor with paramaters to initialize during object creation.


this ---> keyword: used to refer to the current object of a class

Before this:

Object variable  Parameter
brand         brand
color        color

After this:
this.brand -->BMW brand
this.color -->Black color


Access Modifiers:
   --> Java keyword that controls the visibility and accessibility of classes, variables, methods(user-defined method and constructors)
   --> "who can access, what?"

   Modifier        Same class  Same package   Subclass   OtherPackage
      Private        Yes         No              No           No
      Default        Yes         Yes             No           No
      Protected      Yes         Yes             Yes          No
      Public         Yes         Yes             Yes          Yes

Encaptulation:
   --> wrapping data and methods together into a single unit and protect the data form unauthorized access.
   --> Data +secuity + controlled access
   --> achieve by using access modifiers and getter/setter methods

