Inheritance:
    --->  It is the process by which one class acquires the properties and methods of another class.
    Key Terminologies:
    1. Parent Class --> Existing class (eg: Car, Animal)
    2. Child Class --> New class extending parent
    3. Superclass --> Parent
    4. subclass --> child
    5. extends - Java keyword --> creates inheritance

    "IS - A" relationship (eg: Corolla is a car, Dog is a Animal)
Basic Syntex:
    Class ParentClassName {

    }
    Class ChildClassName extends ParentClassName{

    }

    1. Single Inheritance
    2. Multilevel Inheritance
    3. Hierarcial
    4. Multiple Inheritance

 Super Keyword: reference variable that refers to the immediate parent class object

Abstraction:
--> Hide internal implemenations details and show only the necessary functionalities to the user
  "What to do" -->exposed
  "how it is done" --> hidden

Abstract Class:
  --> "Abstract" keyword
  --> cannot be instantiated
  --> It may contain abstract methods.[only Declaration]
  --> It may contain concrete methods
  --> act as blue print for the child classses

Abstract Method:
  --> has only Declaration
  --> does NOT have IMPLEMENTATION.
  --> MUST be implemented by child class

